nodes.title: Model Shared Prefix
widgets_values: masterpiece, high resolution, ultra-detailed, cartoon, toon

# 2. Prompt

The Shared Prefix and Shared Suffix will be added before and after every generation, and should be your model's recommended prompting instructions.

Basic Prompt is your character prompt.

Emotes is the list of emotions Voxta can use. Use `#` before one line to comment it out if you want to experiment.

States is either Idle, Thinking or Talking. You can have several versions of each if you want more variety.

# 1. Model

First, select a model, and a few LORAs.

LORAs are helpful to steer the look of your character for a more coherent style across generations.

# 3. Structure

Provide a base image and set the KSampler denoise to a high value such as 0.95. This will help generations to share the same overall position. You can turn that off by changing Use Image to 2, and setting denoise to 1.

# 3. Sampling

It is recommended to use a fixed seed to minimize differences between generations.

# 4. Output

Go to your character's page in Voxta, and under Assets, copy the path. Use this for voxta_data_path. Subfolder can be Default for most cases.

# Upscale

Not necessary, but can improve the quality by applying an upscale followed by a downscale.

# Face Details

Not necessary, but can improve faces on images where there are many elements. Not necessary for portraits.
